gomodel:SYNGO_2950  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.7: \"Subcellular distribution of BIG2 in neurons by EM immunocyto-chemistry\"\n- \"BIG2 immunolabeling is also locali zed in the postsynapticcytoplasm (f), associated with microtubules (arrowheads), near thepostsynaptic density.\"\n\nFig.8: \"Synaptic distribution of BI G 2 in neurons by EM immunocyto-chemistry\"\n- \"Pre-embedding EM immunoperoxidase labelingwith anti-BIG2 shows immunolabeling at the postsynaptic density(arrows) and dendritic cytoplasm of an asymmetric type I synapse on adendritic spine (a) and of a symmetric type II synapse on a dendriticshaft (b)\"\n- \"Double labe-ling experiments show that BIG2 immunolabeling (arrows , 12 nmdiameter gold particles in f and 18 nm in g and h) is also localizedpresynaptically at GABAergic synapses identified not only by thesymmetric synapse morphology but also by the presence of GABA inthe presynaptic terminal (f, arrowheads, 18 nm gold particles) orGABAARs in the postsynaptic membrane (b 2/3, g and h, arrowheads,10 nm diameter gold particles). \". Experimental description: - \"For Fig. 7(a) and Fig. 8(a and b) 34-day-old male Sprague-Dawley rats were anesthetized...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-23" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2950" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

